---
import PageLayout from '../layouts/PageLayout.astro';
import HeroSection from '../components/HeroSection.astro';
import SignupForm from '../components/SignupForm.astro';
import { donateUrl } from '../data/navigation';
---

<PageLayout title="About Fatmata | Fatmata Barrie for Montgomery County Council" description="Immigration attorney, small business owner, and community leader with 30+ years of service to Montgomery County.">

  <HeroSection title="About Fatmata" subtitle="Leading Change with Purpose and Vision for a Better Tomorrow." />

  <!-- BIO -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container about-row">
      <div class="about-portrait">
        <img src="/images/fatmata-headshot.jpg" alt="Fatmata Barrie" class="portrait-img" />
      </div>
      <div class="about-text prose">
        <p class="section-label">Meet Fatmata Barrie</p>
        <h2>An experienced fighter for Montgomery County.</h2>
        <span class="ornament" style="margin: 0.75rem 0 1.25rem;"></span>

        <p>Montgomery County is a place of opportunity, diversity, and innovation &mdash; but too many residents are struggling with the cost of living, access to quality education, and a government that sometimes feels out of touch.</p>

        <p>I am Fatmata Barrie, and I am running for Montgomery County Council At-Large to ensure that everyone &mdash; regardless of who they are or where they come from &mdash; has the resources and opportunities to thrive.</p>

        <p>Montgomery County has been my home for more than two decades. It's where I built my career, my small business, and my community. Like so many families here, I've seen firsthand the challenges of balancing work, education, and family, and I've dedicated my life to helping others navigate those same challenges.</p>

        <h3 class="about-subhead">My Story</h3>

        <p>My journey to public service began long before I entered politics. I immigrated to the United States from Sierra Leone, West Africa, at the age of 11. Watching my parents work hard while navigating a complex immigration system shaped my belief that government should work for the people it serves.</p>

        <p>After graduating from Florida A&amp;M University with a Bachelor of Science in Psychology and earning my Juris Doctor from the University of Florida Levin College of Law, I dedicated my career to helping families and children access opportunity.</p>

        <h3 class="about-subhead">Career &amp; Advocacy</h3>

        <p>For more than two decades, I have worked as an immigration and special education attorney, helping families stay together, guiding immigrants through the legal system, and advocating for children who need support in our schools. I've also organized free legal workshops and community clinics to ensure families have the information they need to protect their rights and build stable futures.</p>

        <h3 class="about-subhead">Government Service</h3>

        <p>In Montgomery County, I have also served our community in government and civic leadership. I previously worked for Councilmember Will Jawando and served as the Executive Director of the Montgomery County Police Accountability Board and Administrative Charging Committee, helping strengthen transparency and accountability in local government.</p>

        <p>I currently serve on the Montgomery County African Affairs Advisory Group and as an executive member of the African Immigrant Caucus and Immigrant Community Services.</p>

        <h3 class="about-subhead">Community Work</h3>

        <p>As a lifelong Democrat and community organizer, I've worked to bring people into the political process. In 2024, I founded Africans in the Diaspora for Harris, a grassroots network of more than 2,000 members across the country working to engage African diaspora voters.</p>

        <p>I've also been a strong advocate for women, children, workers, and immigrant families. As a board member of the Women's Democratic Club of Montgomery County, I supported efforts to advance paid family leave, paid sick leave, higher wages, and stronger protections for working families.</p>

        <h3 class="about-subhead">Our Shared Future</h3>

        <p>But this campaign isn't just about my story &mdash; it's about our shared future.</p>

        <p>This campaign is about bringing people together &mdash; not dividing us. Montgomery County is stronger when we focus on solutions that work for everyone, whether you've lived here for generations or just arrived.</p>

        <p>I believe in leading with integrity, listening to the people, and making government work for all of us.</p>

        <p>Together, we can build a brighter future for Montgomery County &mdash; one where everyone has a fair shot at success, security, and a place to call home.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- EXPERIENCE -->
  <section class="section section-alt">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="text-center" style="margin-bottom: 3rem;">
        <p class="section-label">Service & Leadership</p>
        <h2>A lifetime of public service.</h2>
        <span class="ornament"></span>
      </div>
      <div class="experience-grid">
        <div class="exp-card">
          <h3>Police Accountability</h3>
          <p>Executive Director of the Montgomery County Police Accountability Board and Administrative Charging Committee.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="exp-card">
          <h3>County Government</h3>
          <p>Worked for Councilmember Will Jawando on policy and constituent services.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="exp-card">
          <h3>African Affairs Advisory Group</h3>
          <p>Current member of the Montgomery County African Affairs Advisory Group and executive member of the African Immigrant Caucus and Immigrant Community Services.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="exp-card">
          <h3>Coalition Building</h3>
          <p>Founded "Africans in the Diaspora for Harris" — a coalition of over 2,000 members mobilizing civic participation.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="exp-card">
          <h3>Women's Democratic Club</h3>
          <p>Board member of the Women's Democratic Club of Montgomery County, supporting efforts to advance paid family leave, paid sick leave, higher wages, and stronger protections for working families.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="exp-card">
          <h3>Community Legal Services</h3>
          <p>Organized free legal workshops and community clinics to ensure families have the information they need to protect their rights and build stable futures.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- WHY I'M RUNNING -->
  <section class="section why-running">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="why-inner">
        <span class="ornament" style="background: var(--gold);"></span>
        <blockquote class="why-quote">
          "I'm running for Council to deliver for the people of Montgomery County. As an immigration and special education attorney, small business owner and community activist for more than 30 years, I know what it means to face uncertainty and still show up for everyone everyday. We need an experienced fighter who will push forward an agenda for a more inclusive community for all and protect the future of Montgomery County."
        </blockquote>
        <cite class="why-attribution">&mdash; Fatmata Barrie</cite>
        <div class="why-ctas">
          <a href="/priorities" class="btn btn-outline-light">See the Priorities</a>
          <a href={donateUrl} class="btn btn-accent">Support the Campaign</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <SignupForm />

</PageLayout>

<style>
  .about-row {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1.5fr;
    gap: 4rem;
    align-items: start;
  }

  .portrait-img {
    width: 100%;
    max-width: 380px;
    border-radius: var(--border-radius);
    border: 3px solid var(--teal);
    box-shadow: var(--shadow-lg);
    margin: 0 auto;
    display: block;
    object-fit: cover;
  }

  .about-text h2 { margin-bottom: 0; }

  .about-subhead {
    font-size: 1.15rem;
    color: var(--teal);
    margin-top: 2rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
    font-family: var(--font-heading);
  }

  .experience-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    gap: 1.25rem;
  }

  .exp-card {
    background: var(--white);
    border: 1px solid var(--light-gray);
    border-radius: var(--border-radius);
    padding: 1.75rem;
    transition: border-color 0.3s, transform 0.2s;
    box-shadow: var(--shadow-sm);
  }

  .exp-card:hover {
    border-color: var(--primary);
    transform: translateY(-2px);
    box-shadow: var(--shadow-md);
  }

  .exp-card h3 { font-size: 1.1rem; margin-bottom: 0.5rem; color: var(--teal); }
  .exp-card p { color: var(--text-light); font-size: 0.95rem; line-height: 1.6; }

  .why-running {
    background: var(--primary);
  }

  .why-inner {
    max-width: 750px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .why-quote {
    font-family: var(--font-heading);
    font-size: clamp(1.1rem, 2.5vw, 1.3rem);
    color: rgba(255,255,255,0.9);
    line-height: 1.8;
    font-style: italic;
    margin: 1.5rem 0 1rem;
  }

  .why-attribution {
    display: block;
    font-family: var(--font-primary);
    font-style: normal;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--gold);
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }

  .why-ctas { display: flex; gap: 1rem; justify-content: center; flex-wrap: wrap; }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .about-row { grid-template-columns: 1fr; gap: 2rem; }
    .experience-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
  }
</style>
